fields: Which one is used for objective things? Which one for subjective things?

大きい for objective.
大きな for subjective.
大きい　vs　大きな

私には大きな夢がある。

Why is this 大きな instead of 大きい？
大きな is used for subjective things.
大きい　vs　大きな
このシャツはちょっと{{c1::大きい}}です。もっと{{c1::小さい}}イサイズはありますか？
大きい and 小さい are used for objective things.
大きい　vs　大きな
to break, to fracture, to break off, to snap off, to pick (e.g. flowers)
counter for flat objects (e.g. sheets of paper)
light (i.e. not heavy), feeling light (i.e. offering little resistance, moving easily)
to get better, to get well, to recover (from an illness), to be cured, to be restored, to heal
to turn over, to turn upside down, to turn up, to turn inside out, to turn out
to close (e.g. book, eyes, meeting, etc.), to shut
to make (the best) use of, to put to good use, to leverage (skills, attributes, experience, etc.), to capitalise on (experience, etc.)
to stick through, to force through
related to, in relation to, as far as ... is concerned
side (of something, or taking someone's side), part
to branch, to fork, to diverge
on good terms (with), on friendly terms (with), (getting along) well, in harmony, happily, peacefully
光と明かりの違いは何ですか？

光：(Natural / talking about light itself) Eg: 太陽の光
明かり：(Manmade / indirect light) ろうそくの明かり
